ritten), Voltage Level (in kV, e.g. 11kV, 22kV, 33kV), LV Switchgear (make, model, and rating), Cubicle Size (dimensions or type code), and Earthing (type and compliance standard)."}, {"title": "Apply 1.5MVA Conditional HV Switchgear Rule", "instructions": "Check the extracted Transformer Size. If it equals 1.5MVA (or equivalently 1500kVA), then regardless of what the drawing shows for HV Switchgear, record HV Switchgear as 'Siemens RLR' and append the note 'OVERRIDDEN per 1.5MVA rule \u2014 Siemens RLR required.' to that field. If the transformer size is not 1.5MVA, record HV Switchgear exactly as written in the Substation Notes."}]}, {"sub_step_number": 3, "sub_step_id": "sub-step-field-check", "sub_step_name": "Assets Field Check Compliance", "phase": 2, "details": "Using the notes extracted in Phase 1, verify that the drawing includes the mandatory assets field-check compliance note. The exact note required is: 'HAVE ALL EXISTING ASSETS BEEN FIELD CHECKED AND ARE ACCURATE AT THE TIME OF DRAWING' answered with 'YES'. Return one of three values: 'YES' (note present, answered YES), 'NO' (note present, answered NO \u2014 flag as non-compliant), or 'NOT FOUND' (note is absent from the drawing \u2014 flag for follow-up).", "required_note_text": "HAVE ALL EXISTING ASSETS BEEN FIELD CHECKED AND ARE ACCURATE AT THE TIME OF DRAWING", "required_answer": "YES", "output_format": "One of: 'YES' | 'NO' | 'NOT FOUND'", "instructional_sub_steps": [{"title": "Search for Field Check Note", "instructions": "Search all extracted notes for the text 'HAVE ALL EXISTING ASSETS BEEN FIELD CHECKED AND ARE ACCURATE AT THE TIME OF DRAWING' or a close paraphrase. This note is typically numbered within the NOTES section and followed by 'YES' or 'NO'. Note: in the drawing the word 'DRAWING' may appear as 'DESIGN' \u2014 treat both as equivalent."}, {"title": "Read and Return the Answer", "instructions": "Once the note is located, read the answer that follows it ('YES' or 'NO'). Return 'YES' if